        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We have set up the spectral windows to achive the best SNR for the dust continumm in the least amount of time possible. One of the spectral windows is set to observe CO 2-1 and another to observe the 13CO and C18O  transitions with a setup that will allow us to resolve the lines to around 10 independent channels for the expected line width. The total bandwidth for these spectral line observations has been kept as large as possible to increase the SNR of the continuum, and  two spectral windows in TDM mode have been added for the same reason. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We request this angular resolution to resolve the disk, which has a radius of around 0.35 arcsec. This is also the size of the largest angular scale we require to image. We have run simulations with CASA to show how we nicely recover the structure of the disk and this is included in the science justification.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The target has an unknown spatial brightness distribution that will be elusidated with these observations. The expected peak brightness is 1.5 or 0.7 mJy per beam based on our transitional disk and edge-on disk model, respectively. Similarly, the outer edge of the disk will have around 0.3 or 0.1 mJy per beam for the transitional and edge-on disk model, respectively.  With the requested 0.02 mJy per beam RMS we will detect this outer part of the disk at a SNR of 5. Meanwhile, in the center of the disk the SNR will range from 35 to 70 again depending on the transitional or edge-on disk model. As for the spectral lines, the peak intensity is estimated from observations of other disks and will be detected at higher SNR than the continuum. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
